## Phase B: Kanban PM Powerhouse (8-12 hours)

### Problem Statement

**Current State:**
- ✅ Kanban board with drag-drop, columns, cards
- ✅ Basic task details (title, description, assignee, due date)
- ✅ Task comments, CSV export (Quick Wins)
- ❌ **NO subtasks** - can't break down large tasks
- ❌ **NO dependencies** - can't show blocked/blocking relationships
- ❌ **NO custom fields** - limited metadata
- ❌ **NO time tracking** - can't track actual vs estimated time
- ❌ **NO filters/search** - hard to find tasks in large boards

**Competitive Gap:**
- Monday.com: Subtasks, dependencies, custom fields, time tracking, advanced filters
- Asana: Subtasks, dependencies, custom fields, timeline view
- Neuman Brain Kanban: 40% feature parity (basic board only)

**Goal:** Move from 40% → 80% Monday.com parity

### Features to Implement

**1. Subtasks** (2-3 hours)
- Checklist-style subtasks within task cards
- Percentage completion indicator (e.g., "3/5 subtasks complete")
- Drag-to-reorder subtasks
- Checkbox to mark complete
- Subtasks persist in store + IndexedDB

**2. Task Dependencies** (2-3 hours)
- "Blocked by" and "Blocks" relationships between tasks
- Visual indicators (🔒 blocked icon, chain link icon)
- Prevent moving blocked tasks to "Done" if blockers not complete
- Dependency graph view (optional Phase 2)

**3. Custom Fields** (2-3 hours)
- Priority field (High/Medium/Low) with color coding
- Effort estimate (Story points: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13)
- Status labels (In Review, Testing, Deployed)
- Custom field builder UI (Phase 2)

**4. Time Tracking** (2-3 hours)
- Estimated time vs actual time
- Start/stop timer for active tasks
- Time spent display (e.g., "2h 30m / 4h estimated")
- Time tracking history log

**5. Filters & Search** (1-2 hours)
- Search by task title/description
- Filter by assignee, priority, status, tags
- Filter by date range (created, due)
- "My tasks" filter (assigned to me)

